{"parentUuid":"e1e0ec8b-96bc-4f0d-a3d3-b800e1043423","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01W8Wdfbp5e7PGpmp29MxrXt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JV9cFtz8tfae1dVtEfAmrL","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/alisha/.marvin/worktrees/skills/search-skills/README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":212,"cache_read_input_tokens":42993,"output_tokens":92,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":212,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":92,"cache_read_input_tokens":42993,"cache_creation_input_tokens":212,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":212},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbE8BuvZsEdD5FhVFMUsj","type":"assistant","uuid":"517ed461-6250-4fab-aa5c-91ecc49e5774","timestamp":"2026-05-20T16:19:36.378Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/.marvin/worktrees/skills/search-skills","sessionId":"1b42a18b-704c-4278-bb92-ed95ac914d02","version":"2.1.145","gitBranch":"search-skills"}
{"parentUuid":"517ed461-6250-4fab-aa5c-91ecc49e5774","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"df0859f1-78cf-42af-b500-858680477522","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JV9cFtz8tfae1dVtEfAmrL","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t![skills cover](assets/gh-repo-cover.png)\n2\t\n3\t# skills\n4\t\n5\tBring your Entire context to your agents with cross-agent skills.\n6\t\n7\t## Why This Exists\n8\t\n9\tThe [Entire CLI](https://github.com/entireio/cli) captures the context behind your\n10\tcode changes: prompts, transcripts,\n11\t[Checkpoints](https://docs.entire.io/cli/checkpoints), and the decisions that led\n12\tto each change, alongside your git history. This repository packages\n13\tagent-invokable workflows that teach coding agents how to use that context across\n14\tdevelopment environments.\n15\t\n16\tInstead of looking up Entire commands yourself, you can ask in plain language and\n17\tlet your agent search prior work, inspect provenance, hand off session state, or\n18\tturn repeated workflows into new skills.\n19\t\n20\t## Install\n21\t\n22\t<<<<<<< HEAD\n23\t### `session-to-skill`\n24\t\n25\tTurns Entire session history into a focused reusable skill draft without making the user manually find, paste, or reconstruct old agent conversations.\n26\t\n27\tCurrent behavior:\n28\t\n29\t- asks what reusable behavior the user wants to extract before reading transcripts\n30\t- accepts an explicit session ID or checkpoint ID when the user already has one\n31\t- searches Entire history with `entire search \"<query>\" --json` when the user describes a repeated workflow\n32\t- expands selected checkpoints with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n33\t- reads active session metadata from `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` when needed\n34\t- extracts durable lessons such as repo conventions, validation commands, user corrections, required inputs, and behaviors to avoid\n35\t- drafts a focused `SKILL.md` instead of recapping the whole session\n36\t- asks before writing, installing, or overwriting a skill\n37\t\n38\t### `explain`\n39\t\n40\tTraces source code back to the original conversation where it was created. Use `/explain` with a function, file, or line of code to understand _why_ it exists.\n41\t\n42\tCurrent behavior:\n43\t\n44\t- identifies the commit that introduced the code via git blame/log\n45\t- reads the session transcript via `entire explain --no-pager --commit <sha>`\n46\t- works with functions, files, and individual line changes\n47\t- reports clearly when code is untracked, uncommitted, or created outside an Entire session\n48\t\n49\t### `what-happened`\n50\t\n51\tExplains what happened to a specific code block by tracing the latest change for a file line,\n52\trange, or pasted snippet through git blame and Entire checkpoints.\n53\t\n54\tCurrent behavior:\n55\t\n56\t- resolves file lines, ranges, or pasted snippets to exact line numbers\n57\t- asks for a concrete file line, range, or snippet before running provenance commands\n58\t- deduplicates commit and checkpoint lookups before running expensive transcript commands\n59\t- asks before expanding broad ranges with many unique commits\n60\t- summarizes `entire explain` output without dumping raw transcripts by default; raw transcript expansion is opt-in\n61\t- falls back to clearly labeled current-code analysis when checkpoint-backed context is unavailable\n62\t\n63\tExamples:\n64\t\n65\t- \"tell me why this code is like that\"\n66\t- \"why does this code look like this?\"\n67\t- \"what happened here: `src/auth.ts:42-57`\"\n68\t- \"what happened at `src/auth.ts:42`\"\n69\t- \"what happened to this block?\" plus a pasted snippet\n70\t\n71\t### `search`\n72\t\n73\tSearches Entire checkpoint history and transcripts to find prior work by topic, repo, branch, author, or time window.\n74\t\n75\tCurrent behavior:\n76\t\n77\t- runs `entire search \"<query>\" --json` and summarizes the top matches\n78\t- supports filters: `--repo`, `--branch`, `--author`, `--date`, and inline query filters like `author:<name>`, `date:week`\n79\t- drills into a specific result with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n80\t- broadens searches progressively when initial results are empty (remove branch filter, widen date, simplify terms)\n81\t\n82\t### `recall`\n83\t\n84\tTurns \"have we done this before?\" into a task playbook by recalling the closest prior session for a described task and synthesizing what worked, gotchas, files touched, and a suggested approach for the new task.\n85\t\n86\tCurrent behavior:\n87\t\n88\t- runs paired `entire search` queries (the original task phrasing plus an alternate phrasing) and deduplicates by checkpoint ID\n89\t- scores hits by topical overlap with recency as a tiebreak, then reads the top 1-3 transcripts via `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager` (falls back to `--raw-transcript`)\n90\t- produces a playbook with sections for closest precedent, what worked, gotchas, files touched, suggested approach, and other relevant precedents\n91\t- broadens progressively (simplify query, drop date filter, drop branch filter) and reports each empty attempt before giving up\n92\t\n93\t### `teach`\n94\t\n95\tBuilds a topic-focused guided lesson from 3-5 canonical checkpoints, with a mental model and patterns to remember rather than a flat list of search results.\n96\t\n97\tCurrent behavior:\n98\t\n99\t- searches over the last month so the lesson uses canonical examples, not just recent activity\n100\t- scores hits by topical specificity (topic in prompt/title), transcript depth, and recency, and prefers diversity (different files, different authors) when picking the 3-5 anchors\n101\t- reads each anchor with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager` (falls back to `--raw-transcript`)\n102\t- produces a lesson with what-you'll-learn, mental model, per-anchor lessons, patterns to remember, and where-to-go-next\n103\t- adds an optional small Mermaid diagram only when the topic has a clear behavioral flow worth illustrating\n104\t\n105\t### `replay`\n106\t\n107\tSteps through a feature's checkpoints chronologically, pausing for questions at each step instead of dumping a summary.\n108\t\n109\tCurrent behavior:\n110\t\n111\t- resolves either a topic (\"how X was built\") or a time window (\"replay last week\"), using `entire dispatch` to derive seed terms when needed\n112\t- builds a chronological sequence of up to 10 checkpoints by default and collapses near-duplicate prompts within a 30-minute window\n113\t- opens with a session card (topic, total steps, date range, primary authors) and then shows step 1 with a paired pause prompt\n114\t- on `next` / `continue` / `yes`, advances; on a question, answers from the current step's transcript only and re-prompts\n115\t- closes with 3-5 journey takeaways generalized across the steps\n116\t\n117\t## Installation\n118\t\n119\tInstall with [skills](https://skills.sh/) CLI (universal, works with any [Agent Skills](https://agentskills.io)-compatible tool):\n120\t=======\n121\tInstall every skill with the [skills](https://skills.sh/) CLI:\n122\t>>>>>>> main\n123\t\n124\t```bash\n125\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --all\n126\t```\n127\t\n128\tInstall one skill:\n129\t\n130\t```bash\n131\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --skill search\n132\t```\n133\t\n134\tSee [Agent-Specific Installation](#agent-specific-installation) for setup\n135\tinstructions by agent.\n136\t\n137\t## Quick Start\n138\t\n139\t> [!NOTE]\n140\t> These skills are most useful in codebases with real\n141\t> [Checkpoints](https://docs.entire.io/cli/checkpoints) and session history. The\n142\t> richer the history, the more context your agent has to work with; in a new or\n143\t> lightly captured repository, some workflows may have less to find or explain.\n144\t\n145\tAfter installing, ask your agent for the workflow you want:\n146\t\n147\t```text\n148\tsearch past work for rate limiting\n149\t```\n150\t\n151\t```text\n152\texplain src/auth.ts\n153\t```\n154\t\n155\t```text\n156\twhat happened here: src/auth.ts:42-57\n157\t```\n158\t\n159\t```text\n160\thand off this session\n161\t```\n162\t\n163\t```text\n164\tturn my release notes workflow into a skill\n165\t```\n166\t\n167\tFor a guided walkthrough, see the\n168\t[skills tutorial](https://docs.entire.io/skills/tutorial).\n169\t\n170\t## What skills help agents do\n171\t\n172\t| Goal | Example prompt |\n173\t| --- | --- |\n174\t| Find prior work before making changes | `search past work for the migration` |\n175\t| Understand the intent behind a function, file, or line | `explain parseConfig` |\n176\t| Investigate the latest change to a specific block | `what happened at src/auth.ts:42` |\n177\t| Pick up another agent's work | `hand off the codex session` |\n178\t| Convert repeated work into a reusable workflow | `make a skill from this session` |\n179\t\n180\t## Included skills\n181\t\n182\tThe current repository includes these skills. Each skill lives in\n183\t`skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`.\n184\t\n185\t### `search`\n186\t\n187\tFinds prior work in your Entire history by topic, repo, branch, author, or time\n188\twindow, so your agent can bring past context into the current task before making\n189\tchanges.\n190\t\n191\thttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/52e50eae-ba53-4f31-ad2e-2a29a767a34f\n192\t\n193\t### `explain`\n194\t\n195\tLooks up the session behind a function, file, or line so your agent can explain\n196\tthe requirement, decision, or original problem that shaped it.\n197\t\n198\thttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ab2e88f6-9bce-417b-ba71-6e93ecad370b\n199\t\n200\t### `what-happened`\n201\t\n202\tStarts from an exact file line, range, or pasted snippet and traces the latest\n203\tchange with `git blame` and Checkpoint context. Useful when reviewing a concrete\n204\tblock, debugging a regression, or asking why that block changed.\n205\t\n206\thttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/47db0daa-60bd-4000-b956-2d0e4d980b9b\n207\t\n208\t### `session-handoff`\n209\t\n210\tReads saved or active session context so another agent can pick up the task\n211\tstate, important discoveries, blockers, and next steps without making you\n212\treconstruct everything manually.\n213\t\n214\thttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0df3b5cd-fe37-4145-af48-138642ccc8bc\n215\t\n216\t### `session-crosslink`\n217\t\n218\tLinks an agent session that ran outside the repo whose commits should record it\n219\t— launched from a higher-level folder, a non-Entire repo, or one repo but\n220\tediting another — to each affected Entire-enabled repo's HEAD commit. Previews\n221\twith `--dry-run` then amends on confirmation, no manual `cd` orchestration.\n222\t\n223\t## Requirements\n224\t\n225\tThese skills are designed for repositories where Entire has captured useful\n226\thistory. Some workflows need:\n227\t\n228\t- the [Entire CLI](https://github.com/entireio/cli) installed\n229\t- a git repository with Entire sessions, Checkpoints, or Checkpoint-backed commits\n230\t- [`entire login`](https://docs.entire.io/cli/commands#login) for workflows that\n231\t  search indexed history\n232\t- a GitHub `origin` and pushed, indexed Checkpoints for remote search results\n233\t\n234\tIndividual skills handle missing context differently and should explain what is\n235\tmissing before falling back or stopping.\n236\t\n237\t## Agent-Specific Installation\n238\t\n239\t<!-- prettier-ignore-start -->\n240\t\n241\t<details>\n242\t<summary>Claude Code</summary>\n243\t\n244\t```bash\n245\t/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n246\t/plugin install entire\n247\t```\n248\t\n249\t</details>\n250\t\n251\t<details>\n252\t<summary>Codex (OpenAI)</summary>\n253\t\n254\tClone into the cross-client discovery path:\n255\t\n256\t```bash\n257\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n258\t```\n259\t\n260\tCodex auto-discovers skills from `~/